WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:10.000
The definition of a function we use today is more or less the one proposed by Peter Lejeune Dirichlet (1805-1859). His main motivation was to unravel the issues surrounding the convergence of the Fourier Series.


00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:18.000
Dirichlet's definition of a function liberates the term from its interpretation as a type of formula.
